# Internal Business Tools Template - Next.js Application

This is a template repository for building internal business tools.

- Code Style
  - Write concise, technical TypeScript code
  - Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes
  - Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication
  - Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError)
  - Keep code organized and consistent across the codebase
  - Keep components focused and composable
  - Use the cn() utility for conditional classNames
  - Every page.tsx page should be a server component, and do data fetching if needed
  - Always return data from fetchers and actions in following format: `{ data: (type of data) | null, error: string | null }`
  - Always wrap fetchers and actions within try-catch block

- Folder Structure
  - All server actions are defined in /lib/actions.ts
  - All fetchers are defined in /lib/fetchers.ts
  - All forms should be defined within /components/forms folder
  - All modals should be defined within /components/modals folder
  - Layout components should be defined within /components/layout folder
  - All configuration files must be defined within /config folder
  - All custom hooks must be defined within /hooks folder
  - Always add css/scss files to /styles folder
  - Always use server actions, avoid API routes unless necessary (e.g. for webhooks)

- Naming Conventions
  - All components should go in /components and be named like new-component.tsx
  - Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/auth-wizard)
  - Don't define custom components within /ui folder
  - Favor named exports for components

- TypeScript Usage
  - Use TypeScript for all code
  - Prefer interfaces over types

- UI and Styling
  - Always use CSS variable-based colors (primary, secondary, accent, background, etc.)
  - Never hardcode hex colors - use Tailwind classes that map to CSS variables
  - Use mobile-first approach for responsive design
  - Make sure everything you produce is mobile-friendly
  - Don't change element sizes on hover
  - Don't use gradients
  - Keep UI consistent across pages
  - Use modern UI/UX design patterns

- Key Conventions
  - Favor server components and Next.js SSR
  - Structure pages as: page.tsx for data fetching, client.tsx for the client component, loading.tsx for loading state
  - Avoid using space-x and space-y, instead use flex and gap
  - Use pnpm
  - Use pnpm lint for linting fixes
  - Always use prisma db push, never use prisma db migrate
  - Never run prisma db push with the accept data loss flag
  - Always build at the end of the task and fix build errors

- Roles
  - ADMIN: Full access to all dashboard pages
  - MEMBER: Access to tasks, action items, recurring tasks, profile
  - VIEWER: Read-only access to tasks, action items, profile
